+## Class: DedicatedWorkers
+
+> Query and receive events from a WebContents' active dedicated workers.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)<br />
+_This class is not exported from the `'electron'` module. It is only available as a return value of other methods in the Electron API._
+
+Instances of the `DedicatedWorkers` class are accessed by using the
+`dedicatedWorkers` property of a `WebContents`.
+
+### Instance Events
+
+#### Event: 'created' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the dedicated worker.
+  * `renderProcessId` number - The Chromium internal process ID of the dedicated worker.
+  * `origin` string - The security origin of the dedicated worker.
+
+Emitted when a dedicated worker has been created.
+
+#### Event: 'destroyed' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the dedicated worker.
+
+Emitted before a dedicated worker is destroyed.
+
+#### Event: 'final-response-url-determined' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the dedicated worker.
+  * `url` string - The final response URL of the dedicated worker script.
+
+Emitted when the final response URL for a dedicated worker script is determined.
+
+### Instance Methods
+
+#### `dedicatedWorkers.getAllRunning()` _Experimental_
+
+Returns `Record<string, DedicatedWorkerInfo>` - A [DedicatedWorkerInfo](structures/dedicated-worker-info.md) object where the keys are the dedicated worker IDs and the values are the information about each dedicated worker.
+
+#### `dedicatedWorkers.getWorkerFromID(id)` _Experimental_
+
+* `id` string - The dedicated worker ID.
+
+Returns [`DedicatedWorkerMain | undefined`](dedicated-worker-main.md) - Instance of the
+dedicated worker associated with the given ID. If there's no associated running
+dedicated worker, this will return `undefined`.
