@@ -0,0 +1,90 @@
+## Class: IpcMainDedicatedWorker
+
+> Communicate asynchronously from the main process to a dedicated worker.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)
+
+This API is a variation of [`IpcMain`](ipc-main.md) targeted for communicating
+with one dedicated worker.
+
+### Instance Methods
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.on(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Listens to `channel`, when a new message arrives `listener` would be called with
+`listener(event, args...)`.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.off(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Removes the specified `listener` from the listener array for the specified
+`channel`.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.once(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Adds a one time `listener` function for the event. This `listener` is invoked
+only the next time a message is sent to `channel`, after which it is removed.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.addListener(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Alias for `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.on`.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.removeListener(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Alias for `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.off`.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.removeAllListeners([channel])`
+
+* `channel` string (optional)
+
+Removes listeners of the specified `channel`.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.handle(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function\<Promise\<any\> | any\>
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerInvokeEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-invoke-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.handleOnce(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function\<Promise\<any\> | any\>
+  * `event` [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerInvokeEvent][ipc-main-dedicated-worker-invoke-event]
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Handles a single `invoke`able IPC message, then removes the listener. See
+`ipcMainDedicatedWorker.handle(channel, listener)`.
+
+#### `ipcMainDedicatedWorker.removeHandler(channel)`
+
+* `channel` string
+
+Removes any handler for `channel`, if present.
+
+[ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event]:../api/structures/ipc-main-dedicated-worker-event.md
+[ipc-main-dedicated-worker-invoke-event]:../api/structures/ipc-main-dedicated-worker-invoke-event.md
