+
+Removes listeners of the specified `channel`.
+
+#### `ipcMainWebContents.handle(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function\<Promise\<any\> | any\>
+  * `event` [IpcMainInvokeEvent](structures/ipc-main-invoke-event.md) | [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerInvokeEvent](structures/ipc-main-dedicated-worker-invoke-event.md)
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+#### `ipcMainWebContents.handleOnce(channel, listener)`
+
+* `channel` string
+* `listener` Function\<Promise\<any\> | any\>
+  * `event` [IpcMainInvokeEvent](structures/ipc-main-invoke-event.md) | [IpcMainDedicatedWorkerInvokeEvent](structures/ipc-main-dedicated-worker-invoke-event.md)
+  * `...args` any[]
+
+Handles a single `invoke`able IPC message, then removes the listener. See
+`ipcMainWebContents.handle(channel, listener)`.
+
+#### `ipcMainWebContents.removeHandler(channel)`
+
+* `channel` string
+
+Removes any handler for `channel`, if present.
