+## Class: SharedWorkers
+
+> Query and receive events from a session's active shared workers.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)<br />
+_This class is not exported from the `'electron'` module. It is only available as a return value of other methods in the Electron API._
+
+Instances of the `SharedWorkers` class are accessed by using the `sharedWorkers`
+property of a `Session`.
+
+### Instance Events
+
+#### Event: 'created' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the shared worker.
+  * `renderProcessId` number - The Chromium internal process ID of the shared worker.
+  * `origin` string - The security origin of the shared worker.
+  * `devToolsToken` string - The DevTools token of the shared worker.
+
+Emitted when a shared worker has been created.
+
+#### Event: 'destroyed' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the shared worker.
+
+Emitted before a shared worker is destroyed.
+
+#### Event: 'final-response-url-determined' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the shared worker.
+  * `url` string - The final response URL of the shared worker script.
+
+Emitted when the final response URL for a shared worker script is determined.
+
+#### Event: 'client-added' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the shared worker.
+  * `frame` WebFrameMain | null - The client frame.
+
+Emitted when a frame starts being a client of a shared worker.
+
+#### Event: 'client-removed' _Experimental_
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` Event\<\>
+  * `id` string - The unique ID of the shared worker.
+  * `frame` WebFrameMain | null - The client frame.
+
+Emitted when a frame stops being a client of a shared worker.
+
+### Instance Methods
+
+#### `sharedWorkers.getAllRunning()` _Experimental_
+
+Returns `Record<string, SharedWorkerInfo>` - A [SharedWorkerInfo](structures/shared-worker-info.md) object where the keys are the shared worker IDs and the values are the information about each shared worker.
+
+#### `sharedWorkers.getWorkerFromID(id)` _Experimental_
+
+* `id` string - The shared worker ID.
+
+Returns [`SharedWorkerMain | undefined`](shared-worker-main.md) - Instance of the
+shared worker associated with the given ID. If there's no associated running
+shared worker, this will return `undefined`.
